[h1 className:"font-lora" style:`{fontSize: 64, textAlign: "center"}`]THE COST OF INCREASING COSTS[/h1]

[p style:`{fontSize: 28, marginBottom: 32}`]Accounting for tuition increases at the 5Cs[/p]

by [Samson Zhang](https://tsl.news/author/samson-zhang/), [Rya Jetha](https://tsl.news/author/rya-jetha/), [Mariana Duran](https://tsl.news/author/mariana-duran/), [Reia Li](https://tsl.news/author/reia-li) and [Jenna McMurtry](https://tsl.news/author/jennamcmurtry/)

[Ava Francis-Hall](https://tsl.news/author/afrancisstudents-pitzer-edu/), [Julia Schwartz](https://tsl.news/author/juliaschwartz/) and [Katherine Tan](https://tsl.news/author/katherine-tan/) also contributed reporting

June 13, 2022

[/div]

Earlier this semester, Pomona College, Claremont McKenna College and Pitzer College announced plans to increase their respective tuition by 4.5 percent for the upcoming 2022-23 school year. Scripps College will follow suit with an increase to its tuition by 3.9 percent, and Harvey Mudd will increase its tuition by 3.5 percent.

The increases are in line with a median tuition increase of 3.7 percent across “top colleges,” according to [a Forbes report](https://www.forbes.com/sites/michaeltnietzel/2022/05/23/published-tuition-at-top-colleges-to-increase-an-average-37-next-year/?sh=24dbe5c61dd8).

Since the 2013-14 school year, tuition has increased by more than 29 percent at each of the 5Cs, outpacing national, Los Angeles County and California inflation rates in the same time period.

